import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin effectiveness against the different bacteria species?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    melted_data = data.melt(id_vars=['Bacteria'], value_vars=['Penicillin', 'Streptomycin', 'Neomycin'], var_name='Antibiotic', value_name='Effectiveness')
    sns.boxplot(x='Antibiotic', y='Effectiveness', data=melted_data)
    plt.title('How does the effectiveness of Streptomycin compare to that of Penicillin and Neomycin?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='Gram_Staining', data=data)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Gram Staining results for the different bacteria species?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    genus_counts = data['Genus'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(genus_counts, labels=genus_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('Which genus of bacteria species is most prevalent in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
